<taxonomicName authority="(Janson, 1907)" baseAuthorityName="Janson" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[151,596,1302,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Oxythyrea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scintillans">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,596,1302,1329]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,408,1302,1329]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Oxythyrea scintillans</emphasis>
(Janson, 1907)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="178" type="duscussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1436,1372,1537]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">
A reference to this taxon listed in 
<bibRefCitation author="Fediere, G. &amp; Lery, X. &amp; Herder, S. &amp; Kouassi, N. K." box="[521,745,1372,1399]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" refId="ref16910" refString="Fediere, G., Lery, X., Herder, S. &amp; Kouassi, N. K. (1989) Cetoines de Cote d'Ivoire (Coleoptera, Cetoniidae, Cetoniinae). Institut International De Resherche Por Le Development a Adiopodoume (IIRSDA), Abidjan, Cote d'Ivoire, number of pages" type="book" year="1989">
Fédière 
<emphasis box="[610,658,1372,1398]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">et al</emphasis>
. (1989)
</bibRefCitation>
from the 
<collectingCountry box="[851,981,1372,1399]" name="Ivory Coast" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Ivory Coast</collectingCountry>
has not been found and is not included in 
<tableCitation box="[151,237,1407,1433]" captionStart="TABLE 4" captionStartId="19.[163,251,163,187]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="TABLE 4. Diversity of Cetoniinae from Ivory Coast, Ghana, and Benin." pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Table 4</tableCitation>
. As this species is absent from the catalogs of 
<bibRefCitation author="Schenkling" box="[751,961,1407,1433]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" refId="ref18446" refString="Schenkling S. (1921) Coleopterorum Catalogus auspiciis et auxilio, W. Junk. Scarabaeidae: Cetoninae editus S. Schenkling Pars 72. W. Junk, Berlin, 431 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 94 - 011 - 9697 - 0 _ 1" type="book" year="1921">Schenkling (1921)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Krajcik, M." box="[972,1130,1407,1433]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" refId="ref17199" refString="Krajcik, M. (1998) Cetoniidae of the world catalogue. Part 1. Typos Studio, Most, 96 + xxxvi pp." type="book" year="1998">Krajčík (1998</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Krajcik, M." box="[1141,1198,1407,1433]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" refId="ref17225" refString="Krajcik, M. (1999) Cetoniidae of the world catalogue. Part 2. Typos Studio, Most, 72 + xxiii pp." type="book" year="1999">1999</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Schoolmeesters, P." pageId="27" pageNumber="178" refId="ref18501" refString="Schoolmeesters, P. (2021) SCARABS: World Scarabaeidae Database. In: Banki, O., Roskov, Y., Vandepitte, L., DeWalt, R. E., Remsen, D., Schalk, P., Orrell, T., Keping, M., Miller, J., Aalbu, R., Adlard, R., Adriaenssens, E., Aedo, C., Aescht, E., Akkari, N., Alonso-Zarazaga, M. A., Alvarez, B., Alvarez, F., Anderson, G. et al, Catalogue of Life Checklis. Version 2021 - 09 - 01. Catalogue of Life. Leiden. https: // doi. org / 10.48580 / d 4 sl- 38 g" type="book" year="2021">Schoolmeesters (2021)</bibRefCitation>
, we believe it is in error.As further evidence, Janson did publish two papers in 1907 (
<bibRefCitation author="Janson, O. E." box="[1166,1321,1441,1468]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" pagination="326 - 338" refId="ref16992" refString="Janson, O. E. (1907 a) List of the Cetoniidae collected by the late Leonardo Fea in West Africa. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, 3 a, 3 (43), 326 - 338." type="journal article" year="1907">Janson 1907a</bibRefCitation>
,b) but this species was not included in either one. Therefore, this record most likely refers to 
<taxonomicName authority="(De Lisle, 1947)" baseAuthorityName="de Lisle" baseAuthorityYear="1947" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Acrothyrea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scintillans">
<emphasis box="[1071,1317,1476,1502]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Acrothyrea scintillans</emphasis>
(De Lisle, 1947)
</taxonomicName>
which is known from the 
<collectingCountry box="[510,642,1511,1537]" name="Ivory Coast" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Ivory Coast</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Beinhundner, G." box="[656,869,1511,1537]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" refId="ref16250" refString="Beinhundner, G. (2017) The Cetoniinae of Africa. Privately published, Euerbach, 1174 + XXIV pp." type="book" year="2017">Beinhundner 2017</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Moretto, P. &amp; Rojkoff, S." box="[881,1160,1511,1537]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" pagination="1 - 123" refId="ref17536" refString="Moretto, P. &amp; Rojkoff, S. (2021) Coleoptera, Cetoniidae (Annexe 3 c). In: Moretto, P., Cosson, B., Takano, H., Basquin, B., Bordat, P., Boucher, S., Bouyer, T., Danflous, S., Derozier, V., Eitschberger, U., Juhel, P., Leroy, E., Limbourg, P., Massa, B., Meunier, J. - Y., Miles, W., Orbach, E., Robiche, G., Rojkoff, S. &amp; Silvestre, G., A threatened forest refuge: The mountain forest at Parinari of Mont Tonkoui in Cote d'Ivoire. Assessment of entomological, botanical and ornithological biodiversity. Site conservation values. Catharsius La Revue, Hors-Serie, 1, pp. 1 - 123." type="journal article" year="2021">Moretto &amp; Rojkoff 2021</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
